2.2 DTCC Message Types & Formats (10 pages)
NOTE: This section requires DTCC TA Services portal access for complete specifications. Initial research based on public documentation and industry standards.

2.2.1 Message Format Overview
Historical Formats

Fixed-width (legacy mainframe): 80-character records
EBCDIC vs. ASCII encoding considerations
Positional field definitions
Modern Formats

XML schemas (ISO 20022 adoption)
JSON payloads (API Marketplace)
Delimited files (CSV, pipe-separated)
Hybrid Approach

Many DTCC systems still use legacy formats
Gradual migration to ISO 20022
Middleware must support multiple formats
