2.2.3 Message Field Dictionary (3 pages)
Common Fields Across Messages:

Transaction ID: Unique identifier (format, length, generation algorithm)
CUSIP: 9-character security identifier (validation: check digit algorithm)
Timestamp: ISO 8601 format, timezone (UTC)
FAST Agent Number: DTC-assigned identifier
Account Number: Format varies (numeric, alphanumeric, length constraints)
Share Quantity: Decimal precision, fractional shares handling
Registration: Name (length limits, special characters), Address (parsing rules), Tax ID (SSN/EIN validation)
Field-Level Validation Rules:

Required vs. optional fields
Data types and constraints
Cross-field validation (e.g., tax ID must match name type)
Conditional requirements (field X required only if field Y = value)
2.2.4 Message Sequencing & Dependencies
Transaction ordering requirements
Idempotency guarantees (can safely retry)
Correlation IDs for multi-message workflows
Timeout and retry policies
2.2.5 Data Flow Diagrams
[DIAGRAMS TO BE CREATED]

1. DRS Deposit Flow (Broker â†’ TA)
   - Broker initiates
   - DTCC validates
   - TA receives notification
   - TA creates account
   - TA confirms completion

2. DRS Withdrawal Flow (TA â†’ Broker)
   - Investor requests via broker
   - Broker submits profile request
   - TA validates ownership
   - TA delivers to DTC
   - Broker receives shares

3. Daily Reconciliation Flow
   - Overnight batch process
   - Position comparison
   - Break identification
   - Exception reporting
   - Resolution workflow

4. Corporate Action Flow
   - Issuer declares action
   - DTCC broadcasts notification
   - TA receives and processes
   - Entitlements calculated
   - Shareholders notified
