SECTION 5: INTEGRATION TIMELINE & PROCESS (3 pages)
5.1 DTCC Onboarding Process (1.5 pages)
5.1.1 Prerequisites
Corporate Requirements

SEC-registered transfer agent (Form TA-1 filed and approved)
Surety bond or insurance coverage (amounts vary by volume)
Fidelity bond (protects against employee dishonesty)
Technical Requirements

Network connectivity capability (mainframe or ANIRA)
Secure infrastructure for certificate storage
Audit logging and recordkeeping systems
5.1.2 Application Process
Step 1: Initial Contact (Week 0)

Contact DTCC Agent Services: [email protected]
Request FAST Agent Application package
Assigned DTCC relationship manager
Step 2: Application Submission (Week 1-2)

Complete FAST Agent Application forms
Submit corporate documents (articles, bylaws, TA registration)
Submit insurance/surety certificates
Technical questionnaire (connectivity method, security measures)
Step 3: DTCC Review (Week 3-6)

DTCC evaluates application
May request additional documentation
Background checks on principals
Operational audit (sometimes site visit)
Step 4: Approval & Setup (Week 7-8)

DTCC assigns FAST Agent Number
Issue mTLS certificates
Provide sandbox access credentials
Technical onboarding call
5.1.3 Timeline Estimate
Total Duration: 8-12 weeks (2-3 months)
Critical Path: SEC TA registration (must be complete first)
Potential Delays: Insurance procurement, DTCC operational audit
5.1.4 Forms & Documentation Required
FAST Agent Application (main form)
Balance Certificate Agreement (choose type: WC-NC, WC-CTA, WC-PROC)
Optional: DWAC Agreement (Deposit/Withdrawal at Custodian)
Optional: DRS/LPA Application (required for Direct Registration System)
Operational Criteria for FAST (attestation)
Insurance documentation (Key Elements of Insurance form)
[NOTE: Obtain copies of these forms from DTCC portal for appendix]

